  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Slice your <strong>aubergine[s]</strong> lengthways into halves (keep the green stalks on)</p><p>Place the <strong>aubergine half[ves]</strong> onto a plate and put the plate in the <strong>microwave </strong>for 5 min</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? You may need to do this in batches!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1646755723234-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1646755723234-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1646755723234-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1646755723234-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1646755723234-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the aubergine is in the microwave, peel and finely dice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced shallot</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until softened, then add the <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for a further 1-2 min</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1646755731864-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1646755731864-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1646755731864-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1646755731864-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1646755731864-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, remove the <strong>aubergine</strong> from the <strong>microwave</strong> and transfer to a baking tray (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!)</p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and put the tray in the oven for 15-16 min or until cooked through, softened and tender</p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1646755739865-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1646755739865-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1646755739865-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1646755739865-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1646755739865-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the shallot and garlic has softened, add your <strong>ground cinnamon</strong> (not a fan of cinnamon? Just add a little!), <strong>ground coriander</strong> and <strong>ground cumin</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, turn the heat up to high, then add your <strong>lamb mince</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1646755748555-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1646755748555-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1646755748555-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1646755748555-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1646755748555-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the lamb mince is browning, dissolve your<strong> beef stock mix</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> with the <strong>tomato paste</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>stock</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>bulgur wheat </strong>to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 7-9 min or until tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return it to the pot</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1646755756037-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1646755756037-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1646755756037-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1646755756037-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1646755756037-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the lamb mince has browned, add the <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>stock</strong> to the pan and cook for 7-8 min or until the sauce has reduced to a bolognese-like consistency and the lamb is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>spiced lamb</strong></p><p>While the sauce is reducing, chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> roughly</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1646755764191-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1646755764191-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1646755764191-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1646755764191-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1646755764191-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add most of the <strong>chopped parsley </strong>(save a little for garnish!)<strong> </strong>and<strong> chopped tomato</strong> to the <strong>drained bulgur </strong>with your <strong>ground sumac</strong>, a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong>, a very generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and mix well – this is your<strong> tabbouleh</strong></p><p>Once the aubergine is cooked through, remove the tray from the oven, then take a spoon and scoop one big spoonful from the <strong>roasted aubergine half[ves] </strong>(careful, it will be hot!)</p><p>Add the scooped <strong>aubergine flesh</strong> to the spiced lamb and mix everything together</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1646756090763-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1646756090763-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1646756090763-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1646756090763-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1646756090763-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To serve, place the<strong> aubergine half</strong> on a plate and stuff with the <strong>spiced lamb mixture</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> tabbouleh</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the<strong> remaining chopped parsley </strong>and season with a generous grind of<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
